                            <comment id="14595726" author="pankaj2461" created="Mon, 22 Jun 2015 10:27:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also in TThreadPoolServer, currently threadKeepAliveTimeSec is hard coded as 60 sec.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;

 &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ThreadPoolExecutor(args.minWorkerThreads,
                                  args.maxWorkerThreads,
                                  60,
                                  TimeUnit.SECONDS,
                                  executorQueue);

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I will raise a Jira in THRIFT project for this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14595948" author="pankaj2461" created="Mon, 22 Jun 2015 14:00:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13700&quot; title=&quot;Allow Thrift2 HSHA server to have configurable threads&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-13700&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-13700&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fix should have considered &quot;hbase.thrift.maxWorkerThreads&quot; if not provided in command line argument. I will address this also in my patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
